OL,3,CWhat it's like living with
OL,4,C'debilitating' locked-in syndrome
OL,6,F"Life in incredibly exhausting and
OL,7,Fdemoralising, everything I do requires
OL,8,Feffort. But I focus on contributing to
OL,9,Fa better future, this drives me to
OL,10,Fkeep going".
OL,12,FThose are the words of Howard Wicks, a
OL,13,F29-year-old man living with locked-in
OL,14,Fsyndrome (LIS).
OL,16,FAt the age of 16, Howard suffered a
OL,17,Fcatastrophic stroke. Every muscle in
OL,18,Fhis body, except for his eyes, became
OL,19,Fparalysed.
