OL,3,CWhat it's like living with
OL,4,C'debilitating' locked-in syndrome
OL,6,FHis only way of communication is
OL,7,Fthrough a computer that tracks his eye
OL,8,Fmovement.
OL,10,FSpeaking to ITV News West Country at
OL,11,Fhis home in Dartmouth, Howard
OL,12,Fdescribes what it is like living with
OL,13,Fthe neurological disorder.
OL,15,F"It is a debilitating syndrome to
OL,16,Fcomprehend," he said. "Being unable to
OL,17,Fmove highlights countless activities
OL,18,Fyou can no longer do. It's absolutely
OL,19,Fhorrendous.
OL,1,W~s1j5 hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}      G2/9
