OL,3,CWhat it's like living with
OL,4,C'debilitating' locked-in syndrome
OL,6,FThrough his charity, Howard said: "We
OL,7,Fprovide grants to assist those in a
OL,8,Flocked in state with financial needs
OL,9,Fsuch as holidays, large pieces of
OL,10,Fequipment and housing adaptations.
OL,12,F"The charity's goal is to support
OL,13,Findividuals in a locked-in state by
OL,14,Fgiving them access to the resources
OL,15,Fand opportunities to live a fulfilling
OL,16,Flife."
OL,18,FAfter his stroke in 2011, Howard's
OL,19,Flife changed drastically. He now lives
OL,20,Falone but requires 24-hour care.
OL,1,W~s1j5 hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}      G5/9
