OL,3,CWhat it's like living with
OL,4,C'debilitating' locked-in syndrome
OL,6,FDespite the unimaginable challenges,
OL,7,FHoward has written a book. It took
OL,8,Faround 18 months to write the 50,000
OL,9,Fwords for 'Hope: Facing the Depths of
OL,10,FAdversity'.
OL,12,FHe used what's called an Eyegaze
OL,13,Fcomputer, which tracks his eye
OL,14,Fmovements.
OL,16,FDescribing the book, Howard said: "The
OL,17,Finitial chapter introduces the reader
OL,18,Fto my life before the stroke allowing
OL,19,Fthem to understand who I was.
OL,1,W~s1j5 hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}      G6/9
